message.content:
cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite games on graphs and their determinacy, which is a central question in game theory and has applications in controller synthesis. 
- cs.LO (Computer Science and Logic) is also likely as the paper discusses conditions under which finite-memory strategies suffice to play optimally, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.SY (Computer Science and Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with controller synthesis and implementable controllers. 
- cs.PL (Computer Science and Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses finite-memory strategies, which correspond to implementable controllers and can be seen as a form of programming. 
- cs.AI (Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with multi-objective settings and optimal play, which are topics that are relevant to AI.
